Package monster

Class monsterData

java.lang.Object
monster.monsterData
public class monsterData extends Object
Represents data for a monster, including its name, health, attributes (strength, agility, magic, vitality), level, experience points given upon defeat, attack type, combat image path, weaknesses, resistances, nullifications, repelled elements, and spells.

      Constructor with arguments annotated with @JsonCreator to deserialize JSON data into a MonsterData object.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the monster.
      health - The health points of the monster.
      str - The strength attribute of the monster.
      agi - The agility attribute of the monster.
      mag - The magic attribute of the monster.
      vit - The vitality attribute of the monster.
      lvl - The level of the monster.
      xpGiven - The experience points given upon defeat.
      attackType - The attack type of the monster.
      combatImagePath - The file path to the combat image of the monster.
      weaknesses - An array representing the weaknesses of the monster.
      resistances - An array representing the resistances of the monster.
      nulls - An array representing the nullified elements by the monster.
      repells - An array representing the elements repelled by the monster.
      spells - An array representing the spells cast by the monster.
